<BasicLayout>
    <PageHeading
        title="About Our Church"
        subTitle="Find more about our church right here"
    />
    <Section heading="Who we are">
        <p>
            Our aim is to lead and train people to become fully devoted
            followers of Jesus Christ. We as a church like to speak the truth to
            people about Jesus Christ. We are a friendly and a welcoming church
            and visitors are always welcome to join us. We invite you to
            experience church at Ebenezer Pentecostal Church no matter where you
            have been or what you have done.
        </p>
        <p>
            We have services every Sunday at 11 am for all and if you are a
            teenager, we invite you to come along to our Youth Gatherings on
            Saturdays at 7.30 pm were we participate in a variety of programs
            such as songs, bible quiz, plays, bible teaching, Christian videos
            and many more.
        </p>
        <p>
            You'd be interested to know that we also run regular prayer meetings
            throughout the year. Check out the site for the dates of the next
            gathering.
        </p>
    </Section>
    <Section heading="Corporate Governance">
        <p>
            Ebenezer Pentecostal Church is a not for profit organisation and
            registered charity (Charity No: SC040609) which subscribes to a high
            standard of accountability and stewardship of its activities and
            finances.
        </p>
        <p>
            The Church Governance is based on the Charity Commission's (OSCR)
            guidelines for good practice and standards and the annual accounts
            are lodged.
        </p>
        <p>
            The Trustees meet a minimum of twice a year to review the financial
            reporting and governance and make sure the standards required are
            being maintained and improved where possible. The board in turn will
            report annually to the members.
        </p>
        <p>
            Ebenezer Pentecostal Church is a Christ centred ministry and
            therefore the trustees and employees are expected to conduct
            themselves with the highest of ethical and biblical standards.
        </p>
    </Section>
    <Section heading="Jesus Lives Forever">
        <p>
            We know God exists, but how can we relate to him? The Bible teaches
            us that God made us and designed us with relationship in mind, not
            just relationship with one another, but with Him, our Creator.
            Because humankind has chosen to live life, in our own way, we've
            missed the God way, hence needing a new way to return to freedom and
            relationship with God.
        </p>
        <p>
            Jesus, the son of God, who the Bible describes as "the visible image
            of the invisible God" entered the human arena to provide just that:
            a way back to relationship with the Father. Jesus, in understanding
            that for us to have relationship with God, a sacrifice needed to be
            given, lived and gave His life for everyone of us, so we could have
            relationship with the Father restored.
        </p>
        <p>
            Restored relationship with our Creator is what is available to us
            all through Jesus even to this day. The bible teaches us that if we
            confess with our mouth what we believe in our heart that Jesus
            Christ is Lord, we can and will be saved from our current life and
            into newness of life - the life we were made for. If you would like
            to start that journey of relationship with God, you can do that
            today. It's the most amazing step, that acknowledges your need of
            God and your desire to walk with him in relationship from this day
            forward. If that's you, with all your heart speak the following
            prayer to God today:
            <blockquote>
                Jesus, I thank you that you died for me, so that I could have a
                relationship with God restored. Today, I give myself to you and
                commit to walk with you all the days of my life. In your name I
                ask. Amen!
            </blockquote>
        </p>
        <p>
            If you have made that decision in your heart today, it's the best
            decision you could ever make and the start of a whole new journey
            with God at your side. We would love to hear from & celebrate with
            you and help you in your next steps.
        </p>
    </Section>
